The contradiction lies between Evidence 11 (Autopsy Report) and Testimony 3 ("Is there any person who could survive such an injury?"). In Testimony 3, Gravelle implies that the wounds were fatal and that nobody could survive them. However, Gravelle later asks the reader to review the autopsy report (Evidence 11), which may reveal a detail that contradicts the assumption that the wounds were immediately fatal (such as time of death, survival timeframe, or another cause).

